Avion Express is a charter and aircraft lease operator based in Vilnius Lithuania. Its former name was Nordic Solutions Air and was rebranded in 2008. In 2010 the company was bought by the French investment group Eyjafjoll SAS.
Prime Directive Records is an independent record label based in Balboa CA.
Adams County Transit Authority is a regional public transportation agency that operates bus service in Adams County Pennsylvania.

Star Vault is a Swedish games company founded by its CEO Henrik Nystrom. Star Vault is the creator of Mortal Online a first-person fantasy MMORPG using Unreal Engine 3. Mortal Online launched June 9 2010.

Infitec GmbH is a German company that specializes in 3-dimensional technology. It owns a technique for channel separation in stereo projection based on interference filters (Interference filter technology).
Kinneret Zmora-Bitan Dvir is one of Israel's largest book publishing companies.

Recon Instruments is a Canadian technology company which introduced the world’s first Heads-up Display (HUD) products to a consumer market. The company has developed HUD solutions which provide hands-free performance stats navigation and communications information direct-to-eye in real-time.
Communology (based in Cologne Germany) operates worldwide as supplier of rich-media mobile communication applications for multiple platforms including Symbian Java ME Windows Mobile and Android.
MSE is an acronym for Measuring and Scientific Equipment (UK) Ltd. For other Acronyms of MSE see MSE (Disambiguation)
LayerOne Inc. acquired by Switch & Data NASDAQ: SDXC in 2005 was a U.S. private corporation that provides carrier-neutral datacenters and interconnection.
Rutubo Games (ゲームのるつぼ Gêmu no Rutsubo) is a video game developer that was formed partially by former Dempa employees. Rutubo's focus has been on porting arcade conversions mainly for Sega.

Free b (Welsh: Bws am ddim Free bus) was a zero-fare shuttle bus that operated in Cardiff city centre Wales. The route circled the edges of the city centre anti-clockwise. The service was operated by Cardiff Bus.
L'Est Films Group Int’l Co is a company in entertaining industry also known as “EFG” which has movie distribution and production two major services.
Ansaldo was one of Italy's oldest and most important engineering companies existing for 140 years from 1853 to 1993.

Flux is a software company that develops and licenses software products targeted for the Workflow Workload Automation Managed File Transfer and eBAM markets. Headquartered in Las Vegas Flux also has offices in Boulder Buenos Aires Hawaii Memphis and Montana.

Znanie (Russian: Зна́ние; English: Knowledge) was a publishing company based in St. Petersburg Russia founded by Konstantin Pyatnitsky and other members of the Committee for Literacy. It operated from 1898 until 1913.

The Zezë is a river in western Albania a source river of the Ishëm River. Its source is in the mountains east of Krujë. It flows through Fushë-Krujë and joins the Gjole near Kodër-Thumanë to form the Ishëm.
Lake Matapédia is a body of water in Quebec Canada and is the source of the Matapédia River. The town of Amqui lies at the southeast corner of the lake.
The River Darent or River Darenth is a Kentish tributary of the River Thames in England. Its name is believed to be from a Celtic word meaning 'river where oak-trees grow' (compare Derwent).
Thorvaldson Lake is a fresh water lake in Northern Saskatchewan named after Thorbergur Thorvaldson in 1966.

Lake Fianga is a lake in Chad and Cameroon. It does not have clearly delineated borders as it forms the western border of an area of permanent swampland. The lake forms with the seasonal flooding of the Logone River.
Kuortaneenjärvi is a medium-sized lake in the Lapuanjoki main catchment area. It is located in the Southern Ostrobothnia region in Kuortane Finland.
Lake Rototuna Lower is a lake in the Northland Region of New Zealand.
The Valea Seacă River or Hăigaş River is a tributary of the Crişul Negru River in Romania.
Lõõdla is a lake of Estonia.
Kieferbach is a river of Bavaria Germany.

Katzensee is a lake on the border of the city of Zurich and Regensdorf in the Canton of Zurich Switzerland. Its surface area is 0.36 km². 						16x Media related to Katzensee at Wikimedia CommonsTemplate:Portal:Switzerland/Stub
McClure Pass (el. 2671 m./8755 ft.) is a high mountain pass in the Rocky Mountains of western Colorado in the United States.
The Iad River is a tributary of the Bistriţa River in Romania.
The Cristeasa River is a tributary of the Storhașu River in Romania.
Brûlé Lake is a lake in western Alberta Canada.
The Arroio Pelotas is a river of Rio Grande do Sul state in southern Brazil.
The Petrus- en Pauluskerk (English: Peter and Paul Church) is a church in Loppersum in the Netherlands. It is a rijksmonument and in the Top 100 Dutch heritage sites.

The Liberty Hall Museum in Union Union County New Jersey United States is an American historic site. Built in 1772 as a fourteen-room Georgian-style house Liberty Hall stands today a fifty-room Victorian Italianate mansion.
Adelaide Provincial Hospital is a Provincial government funded hospital for the Nxuba Local Municipality area in Adelaide Eastern Cape in South Africa.

EP 09 Towers is a complex of six towers spreading across a built-up area of 450000 square meters. The mixed-use community will have one residential community and the other two which include retail commercial and entertainment amenities.

BRAC Bhaban is a commercial-use building located in Dhaka Bangladesh. It is one of the tallest buildings in Dhaka with a height of 64 m (210 ft).The building has 20 floors which are used for commercial purposes.
Ringve Museum is Norway's national museum for music and musical instruments with collections from all over the world.
The George Clayson House located at 224 East Palatine Road in Palatine Illinois is a Second Empire home built in 1873 that has been restored to its 1890-1900 appearance.

Gārsene Manor is a Neo-Gothic manor house located in the historical region of Selonia in Latvia. The palace houses a museum where visitors can view an exhibition about the Baltic-German von Budberg family.
Radisson Blu is a five-star hotel in Chennai India. It is located at on GST Road at Meenambakkam 2 km from Chennai International Airport.
Oakey Streak Methodist Episcopal Church is a historic Methodist church in Greenville Alabama. It was built in 1875 and added to the National Register of Historic Places in 1980.
The Jerome Park Reservoir is located in Jerome Park a neighborhood in the North Bronx New York City.
Burg Perchtoldsdorf is a castle in Lower Austria Austria.
The Château de Rousson is a castle in the commune of Rousson in the Gard département of France.

The Ylikiiminki Church is an evangelical Lutheran church in Ylikiiminki Oulu.The wooden cruciform church has been designed by Jacob Rijf an Ostrobothnian architect and builder of churches. The church was completed in 1786.

Cathedral Historic District is a 32 acres (13 ha) historic district in Dubuque Iowa USA that was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1985. It includes 96 contributing buildings including St. Raphael's Cathedral
The Stovall House is a historic home in Tampa Florida. It is located at 4621 Bayshore Boulevard. On September 4 1974 it was added to the U.S. National Register of Historic Places.

Robert Uno Normann (born 27 June 1916 in Sundløkka in the former Borge kommune now Fredrikstad deceased 20 May 1998 in Sarpsborg Norway) was a Norwegian guitarist and is considered one of the jazz guitar pioneers.

Charity Brown (born Phyllis Boltz in Kitchener Ontario) is a Canadian film actress singer and voice artist for television animation shorts. She is one of Eastwood Collegiate Institute's notable alumni.
Trevor Moran (born September 30 1998) is an American recording artist and YouTube personality.

Geoffrey 'Geoff' Stephens (born 1 October 1934 in New Southgate North London) is an English songwriter and record producer most prolific in the United Kingdom in the 1960s and 1970s.
Syl Johnson (born July 1 1936) is an American blues and soul singer and record producer.
Ambrose McCarthy Patterson (29 June 1877 – 26 December 1967) was a painter and printmaker.

Geri Doran was born in Kalispell Montana in 1966. Doran has attended Vassar College the University of Cambridge the University of Florida (MFA 1995) and Stanford University where she held a Wallace Stegner Fellowship in Poetry.
Dmitri Petrovich Savitski (Russian: Дмитрий Петрович Савицкий (born January 25 1944) (Russian: Дми́трий Петро́вич Сави́цкий) is a Russian writer and poet.
Claudia Moscovici(born June 1 1969) is a Romanian-American novelist and art/literary critic.
Jason Shiga is an Asian American cartoonist who incorporates puzzles mysteries and unconventional narrative techniques into his work.
Shabana Rehman Gaarder (Urdu: شبانه رحمان) (born 14 July 1976 in Karachi Pakistan) is a Norwegian stand-up comedian writer and columnist.

Elizabeth Rider is an English actress best known for her recurring role as DI Lynette Driver in the BBC soap opera Doctors which she has appeared in 2009 and often from 2010.
